# Characterization tests — spring-music Album API
# Format: REST Client (VS Code) / JetBrains HTTP Client
# Run against: http://localhost:8080 (legacy monolith with ./gradlew bootRun)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080

### GET all albums — should return JSON array with id, title, artist, genre, trackCount, releaseYear
GET {{baseUrl}}/albums
Accept: application/json

###

### GET single album — replace {id} with a real id from the list above
# GET {{baseUrl}}/albums/{id}
# Accept: application/json

###

### GET non-existent album — should return 404
GET {{baseUrl}}/albums/nonexistent-000
Accept: application/json

###

### POST create album — should return created album with server-assigned id
POST {{baseUrl}}/albums
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Characterization Test Album",
  "artist": "Test Artist",
  "releaseYear": "2024",
  "genre": "Test",
  "trackCount": 1
}

###

### PUT update album — replace {id} with id from POST response
# PUT {{baseUrl}}/albums/{id}
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "id": "{id}",
#   "title": "Updated Title",
#   "artist": "Test Artist",
#   "releaseYear": "2024",
#   "genre": "Test",
#   "trackCount": 2
# }

###

### DELETE album — replace {id} with id from POST response
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/albums/{id}
